Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.040 --> 00:00:08.760
It's a fairly natural question. If you're looking at the sequence of prime numbers, so, P1 is 2, P2 is 3, and so on,

00:00:09.060 --> 00:00:11.480
how big do these gaps get?

00:00:11.960 --> 00:00:19.840
And we know that, actually, the gaps can get pretty big. So there's a very high school argument, that if you take the numbers 1

00:00:20.170 --> 00:00:27.180
times 2 times 3, up to, say, times 100, and then you look at this number

00:00:27.400 --> 00:00:30.389
plus 2, this is going to be a multiple of 2,

00:00:30.910 --> 00:00:33.029
because 2 is a multiple of 2, and

00:00:33.219 --> 00:00:39.419
this first big number of product of numbers between 1 and a hundred is multiple of 2. Another way that mathematicians might write this is

00:00:40.149 --> 00:00:42.718
100 exclamation mark plus 2.

00:00:43.329 --> 00:00:46.648
So this is, multiply all numbers up to 100 together, and then add 2.

00:00:47.170 --> 00:00:49.680
But then exactly the same argument means that

00:00:50.440 --> 00:00:52.149
100 factorial

00:00:52.149 --> 00:00:54.628
plus 3 is going to be a multiple of 3.

00:00:54.879 --> 00:00:59.459
And so, 100 factorial plus 2 can't be prime, because it's a multiple of 2, and it's bigger than 2.

00:00:59.920 --> 00:01:01.920
100 factorial plus 3 can't be prime,

00:01:02.230 --> 00:01:08.430
because it's a multiple of 3 and bigger than 3. And similarly, you can go all the way on to

00:01:08.950 --> 00:01:10.119
100 factorial

00:01:10.119 --> 00:01:11.320
plus

00:01:11.320 --> 00:01:18.389
100, and this can't be a prime, because it's a multiple of 100 and bigger than 100. And so this is

00:01:18.880 --> 00:01:23.909
99 consecutive numbers, none of which can be prime numbers. And so you know that

00:01:24.549 --> 00:01:28.049
there has to be this gap between prime numbers of size at least 100.

00:01:28.689 --> 00:01:34.199
But, obviously, you can replace 100 here with any number you like, and that shows that there are

00:01:34.540 --> 00:01:36.485
arbitrarily large gaps between prime numbers.

00:01:36.485 --> 00:01:39.209
