00:01:39.210 --> 00:01:40.950
"You've proven that they are..."

00:01:40.950 --> 00:01:47.880
Right. So this is completely a rigorous mathematical proof, that whatever number you like, take a million,

00:01:47.880 --> 00:01:49.030
take a billion,

00:01:49.030 --> 00:01:51.689
there exists a prime gap which is

00:01:51.909 --> 00:01:57.298
bigger than a billion, or bigger than a million, or bigger than a billion billion billion, or bigger than the number of atoms in the

00:01:57.299 --> 00:02:00.959
universe. And so there are these really huge gaps between prime numbers,

00:02:01.719 --> 00:02:04.469
but the prime numbers where these gaps occur may be

00:02:05.200 --> 00:02:06.630
really huge themselves.

00:02:07.120 --> 00:02:09.479
And then there's this question as to, okay,

00:02:09.479 --> 00:02:15.659
if I have a prime number of about a million digits, how big can the

00:02:16.030 --> 00:02:19.709
gaps between prime numbers be? For example, if you're trying to find a prime number,

00:02:20.200 --> 00:02:24.269
let's say, I challenge you to find, find a prime number that's size about a million.

00:02:24.489 --> 00:02:26.669
One way you might try and go about it is,

00:02:27.340 --> 00:02:31.349
take a million, try and test if it's prime, if it's not prime,

00:02:31.720 --> 00:02:37.769
and a million's not prime, test a million and one, test a million and two, test a million and three, until you find a prime number.

00:02:38.620 --> 00:02:43.319
And, this is actually, we believe, a pretty good way of finding prime numbers, that it's completely deterministic,

00:02:43.319 --> 00:02:45.319
you can do it quite quickly on a computer.

00:02:45.400 --> 00:02:50.429
Maybe takes you a while by hand when they, after the millions, but a computer can do this very quickly.

00:02:51.400 --> 00:02:52.840
However,

00:02:52.840 --> 00:02:55.200
mathematically, our theoretical understanding of this is

00:02:56.110 --> 00:02:59.429
pretty poor at the moment, and it could be the case that you have to go on

00:02:59.680 --> 00:03:04.980
ages and ages before you find a prime number, if there were these really large gaps between prime numbers.

